VSri Rama Kala Vedike has organised a music programme coinciding with the 30th death anniversary of the tabla player Ramachandra Yavagal. This programme organised by his son Ravindra Yavagal, the leading tabla player of the State will feature a tabla solo by Vikas Naregal, sitar recital by Ankush N. Nayak, and vocal recital by Radha Desai and Shakti Patil.The accompanists to these musicians will be Shashibhushan Gurjar and Madhusudhan on the tabla, Narasimha Kulkarni on the harmonium and Faiyyaz Ahmed Khan on the sarangi.The main part of the programme constitutes a felicitation to Pandit Mahadeva Indorkar of Mumbai. He will be given the Kalashringa award for his contribution to tabla. This award which is given every year in the name of Ramachandra Yavagal, was conferred upon Rajeev Taranath last year.Born in 1932 in Indore, Pandit Indorkar was a child prodigy. He gave his first performance when he was 12. Initially trained under his father Narayanarao Indorkar, he has his later lessons under Ustad Jahangir Khan and Ustad Gami Khan. Pandit Mahadeva Indorkar even learnt vocal classical music at Vyas Sangeet Vidyalaya, Mumbai.He was the staff artiste of All India Radio till 1990 and has been part of several music conferences. He even lead a cultural delegation to China.Pandit Indorkar has accompanies legends like Ustad Amir Khan, Ustad Bismillah Khan, Pandit V.G. Jog, Gangubai Hangal and Ustad Vilayat Khan.These concerts will be held at Bhumika, Malleswaram 17th Cross, on April 29, 5 p.m.Bottom Template Starts
